    <section property="schema:articleBody" class="articleContainer">
      <section id="Objectives" class="leftColumn">
        <h2>OD4D Objectives</h2>
          <p>The new OD4D platform should be inclusive and accessible to provide a common space for the open data community, which will serve as a reference for individuals and institutions interested in putting into practice concepts of data on the web, open data and transparency.</p>
          <p>The platform serves as a hub for investors, governments, institutions and individuals who intend to work together to create a collaborative network around the theme.</p>
          <p>To this end, the overall objectives of the platform are:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>To aggregate initiatives of data on Web, from partner organizations and individuals, demonstrating in detail the step by step of structuring open data use cases;</li>
            <li> To promote integration and dissemination of knowledge on open data using native languages;</li>
            <li>To promote standards and specific vocabularies;</li>
            <li>To be a reference about open data;</li>
            <li><em>To be an open data case itself.</em></li>
          </ul>
          <p>The expected final result will be <em>the use of a Open Data website as a case for Open Data, connecting networks with innovative resources to foster the Open Data value chain.</em></p>
      </section>

      <section id="Specific-Tasks" class="rightColumn">
        <h2>Goals</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The od4d.org new platform will serve as connection among regional open data initiatives in Latin America, Africa, Asia and the Caribbean.</li>
          <li>The site will be a case of Open Data itself, transforming it's data in one open repository of knowledge, always respecting privacy guidelines.</li>
          <li>The new OD4D platform will bring a new experience for the user of the Open Data for Development Network. Through a multilingual website, we expect that it will connect people and foster the open data ecosystem.</li>





        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="Intended-Results">
        <h2>Intended results:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
          Raising awareness among governments and civil society of the usefulness and potential of Open Data in public policies.
          </li>
          <li>
          Supporting capacity building for the opening and the “meaningful use” of government Data.
          </li>
          <li>
          Fostering the development of new data opening initiatives in the region, with a long-term and sustainable perspective.
          </li>
        </ul>
